    • Method Detail

      • getFillTextFillNamedEntities

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getFillTextFillNamedEntities()
        Gets the named entity types that are asked for within fill text concept questions.
        Example original sentence: The capital of Germany is <LOCATION>Berlin</LOCATION>.
        Berlin as location would be offered for the filltext if location is contained within the properties values.
        The resulting fill text question would be: "What is the complete sentence? The capital of Germany is ___?".
        Returns:
        a list of named entities

      • getFillTextFillPartOfSpeechTags

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getFillTextFillPartOfSpeechTags()
        Gets the part of speech tag typesthat are asked for within fill text concept questions.
        Example original sentence: The capital of Germany is <NNP>Berlin</NNP>.
        Berlin as a proper noun singular would be offered for the filltext if location is contained within the properties values.
        The resulting fill text question would be: "What is the complete sentence? The capital of Germany is ___?".
        Returns:
        a list of named entities

      • getCardinalRelationCompositePosTags

        Gets the configured part of speech tags that can be represented by a cardinal relation.
        E.g. the sentence <NN>Germany</NN> has 16 <NN>states</NN> -> here, the composite part of speech tag is NN (for noun).
